@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Eclairium" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. The only requirement is that your Workbench
must have at least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  Gamewplay is very simple: just click on the 'cloud' icons located at
the top of the game board, this will generate a lightning bolt. If it
touches any tiles that contain coloured patterns, these tiles will be
eliminated and will be removed from the game board.

  You get points according to the number of tiles that are eliminated
by a lightning bolt. If there are 2 or more tiles of the same type,
the more points you will get (2 tiles = 4 points, 3 tiles = 8 points,
4 tiles = 16 points, and so on).

  When no tiles are eliminated, some tiles will be added on the game
board. That number of tiles will double, until at least one tile is
eliminated. However, the number of added tiles will stay the same,
except when at least 2 tiles get eliminated, which will reset the
number of added tiles to zero.

  As the game progress, some 'undestructible' tiles (looking like ice
cubes) will appear. Lightning bolts will pass through those tiles
without affecting them... as these tiles are undestructible, they
will remain where they are until the end of the game...

  To complicate matters a bit more, some clouds may disappear.
However, occasionally, a cloud may reappear somewhere... perhaps maybe
not where you really want it, but one thing is certain: there will
always be at least one cloud present at all time.

  The game ends when the game board is completely filled, or when it
is empty (or there are only undestructible tiles)... in the case of an
empty board, the final score is doubled.

  Have fun!

@endnode

